SIMPLE: nay
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nay
<hw>nay</hw> <pr>(n⟦amac⟧)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>nei</ets>; akin to E. <ets>no</ets>. See <er>No</er>,
<pos>adv.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>No; -- a negative answer to a
question asked, or a request made, now superseded by
<altname>no</altname>. Opposed to <ant>aye</ant> or <ant>yea</ant>. See
also <er>Yes</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>And eke when I say ⟦ldquo⟧ye,⟦rdquo⟧ ne say not
⟦ldquo⟧<qex>nay</qex>.⟦rdquo⟧</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I tell you <qex>nay</qex>; but except ye repent, ye shall all
likewise perish.</q> <rj><qau>Luke xiii. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And now do they thrust us out privily? <qex>nay</qex>, verily; but
let them come themselves and fetch us out.</q> <rj><qau>Acts xvi.
37.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that will not when he may,⟦br⟧
When he would he shall have <qex>nay</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Old
Prov.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Before the time of Henry VIII. <xex>nay</xex> was used
to answer simple questions, and <xex>no</xex> was used when the form of
the question involved a negative expression; <xex>nay</xex> was the
simple form, <xex>no</xex> the emphatic.</note>
<rj><au>Skeat.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not this merely, but also; not only so, but; -- used
to mark the addition or substitution of a more explicit or more emphatic
phrase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Nay</xex> in this sense may be interchanged with
<xex>yea</xex>. ⟦ldquo⟧Were he my brother, <xex>nay</xex>, my kingdom's
heir.⟦rdquo⟧</note> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nay</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nay
<hw>Nay</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Nays</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Denial; refusal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A negative vote; one who votes in the
negative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>It is no nay</b></col>, <cd>there is no denying it.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>haucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nay</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Nay
<hw>Nay</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To refuse.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holinshed.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nayaur</ent>⟦br⟧
